  "body": "### Description\nAs a Teku User, I want dependencies between options to be clear so that when I specify an option that requires another option to be specified, this is clearly identified. \n\neg can you currently specify --p2p-port WITHOUT --p2p-enabled (or p2p-enabled set to false) \nin which case the port is ignored\n\n### Acceptance criteria\n* if I specify any other --p2p option without --p2p-enabled I get an error with explanation and Teku does not start\n* if I specify --p2p-enabled and there are other options required, then I get an error message saying any --p2p options that are required (I think for p2p they all have defaults so this may not be an issue)",
